The paper discusses ad-hoc retrieval systems and rank aggregation functions, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also introduces concepts related to graph-based representations and indexing, which are relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes an efficient retrieval method, which is likely to be of interest to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community.
